inputs.text: Our good friend and award winning mixologist Walter Pintus @waltz16 is back to show you how to make crystal clear quality ice in just a few simple steps*  *We considered carving this block into an ice sculpture of a swan, but we realised a Caorunn and tonic is just as impressive.   This method is called ‚Äúdirect freezing‚Äù - where the source of energy is pulled directly from one side only.  You will need: 5L ice cooler box - Home freezer  1. Remove the top lid from the cooler box. 2. Fill the cooler with tap water and place it in the freezer.  3. After 24h Remove the ice cooler from the freezer and let it rest for 15min at room temperature. 4. Flip the cooler upside down in order to extract the block. 5. With a spoon or a fork Remove the watery / cloudy bottom part of the block (here is we‚Äôre all the impurities are concentrated). 6. Now all you‚Äôre left with is a big slab of crystal clear ice. 7. Portion it in small and big cubes.  For more #LifeHacks, click on through to our website üíª

We‚Äôre so grateful to our whole team for going above and beyond this week while we problem solve and work off-site to get tails finished and ready to ship to you! inputs.text: Repost from @abby.of.finfolk ‚ú®  ‚ÄúWorking through the last of the custom Mythics on my to-do list and loving the teal and bronze color palette for this one.ü§é  Painting, for me, is a labor of love. It‚Äôs both my greatest joy and the hardest work I do. When we first started Finfolk, Bryn was the sculptor and I was the painter, and we‚Äôve kept those respective titles (while gaining about a dozen more each) over the last nine years. Since 2012, almost everything that‚Äôs come out of Finfolk has been hand painted by me, with the exception of some occasional assistant work.   The physical labor of painting is where the true ‚Äúwork‚Äù of painting lies. First the gear- mask, goggles, gloves, a full paint suit, and a loud compressor. Then my physical surroundings- the hard concrete pad of my painting deck, and whatever weather conditions or temperatures we may be experiencing on a paint day. I wear ice packs in anything above 80¬∞ and generally try to avoid painting in anything below 40¬∞, because the cold metal from the paint gun will cause my hands to go numb. There are days where my back and shoulders ache from bending over tables, and other days where my hips and knees ache from spending hours standing mostly stationary. (And more and more days lately when it‚Äôs both.)  But there are also many moments - blissful and transportive ones, where painting becomes meditative. A release from the stress of ‚Äúupstairs,‚Äù and into an easy rhythm of creative flow. I often joke that there are some flukes I could paint with my eyes closed, because of how often I‚Äôve painted them. But there‚Äôs almost a comfort in the muscle memory of each paint stroke. It‚Äôs as much a part of me as I am of it. üñ§‚Äù

This policy covers any FILE or FILE FRAGMENT that you have saved on your hard disk or the network.  (4) DATABASES: do not delete any information in DATABASES.  (5) EXCEL SPREADSHEETS: do not delete any information in EXCEL SPREADSHEETS.  (6) CALENDARS OR SCHEDULING PROGRAMS: do not delete any information.  (7) OTHER ELECTRONIC DATA: do not delete any OTHER ELECTRONIC DATA.  (8) HARD DRIVE CAPACITY: in the event that you run out of disk space on your personal computer, you may copy files to the network (where they will be backed up), then delete the files from your personal computer to create the work space you need.  DO NOT DELETE ANY FILE BEFORE YOU HAVE COPIED IT TO THE NETWORK.

These animals carry seeds on them or in their digestive system and release them into the reforested area. The dispersed seeds begin to sprout and grow alongside our restored forest. We also discovered that many of the planting areas contain dormant seeds or root systems in the soil. inputs.text: No one in need was ever turned away from Shannon‚Äôs house‚Äîher father welcomed and provided for everyone. Inspired by his example, Shannon always asks herself, "What can I do to support someone else?"  "I don't know how to turn it off. There's people hurting," she says. "If we have it to give, it's not for us to hold it for ourselves."  When Shannon isn't serving her partners (employees) as a partner resources manager, she's serving meals to under resourced families through her church, raising scholarship money through her kid's soccer club, buying equipment for local schools and providing necessities to women in transitional housing with her Sisters of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Inc. She is also an active member of her regional employee network, a certified life coach and a kidney donor.  "We serve, because we're not meant to do life alone," says Shannon. "My heart and passion is to be of service and support others. That has been my joy."  For Black History Month we're celebrating our partners and their stories as they share what everyday Black excellence means to them. #BlackHistoryMonth

inputs.text: Your classic V-Day treat, now plant-based. Grab the recipe for these Heart-Shaped Truffles below or on our blog! üíñüç´ ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä Ingredients *1 3-ounce dairy-free dark chocolate bar, finely chopped  *3 tablespoons Califia Farms Vanilla Better Half  *4 ounces dairy-free semi sweet chocolate chips  *1 teaspoon coconut oil  *1 12 count (¬Ω cup capacity) heart shaped silicone mold  *Flaky sea salt, optional  *Dried rose petals, optional    Method *Add the chopped chocolate bar to a medium bowl. Warm up the Califia Farms Vanilla Better Half in the microwave for 30 seconds. *Pour the warmed Vanilla Better Half over the chopped chocolate and let sit for a minute. Whisk the chocolate until a glossy ganache forms. Transfer the ganache to a piping bag and fill each of the molds.  *Place in the freezer until firm, about 30 minutes. Once the ganache hearts are set, carefully remove and transfer to a pan covered with parchment paper.  *Add the chocolate chips and coconut oil to a microwave-safe bowl and microwave for 30 seconds. Remove the bowl, mix, and microwave again. Repeat this process until the chocolate is smooth and glossy. Let cool for 2-3 minutes. *Quickly roll each heart in the melted chocolate, one at a time, then lift out of the chocolate, letting any excess drip off. Transfer to the prepared pan and sprinkle with sea salt or dried rose petals immediately.  *Once complete, place the chocolate in the fridge to fully set before enjoying, about 10 minutes.

inputs.text: Our new Blue Plate Special is PUPUSAS! What‚Äôs a pupusa, you may wonder?  You know that we‚Äôre an American diner, but you may not know that we‚Äôre a very diverse team here, hailing from many countries. For example, our Kitchen Mgr., Luis, is from El Salvador. We asked him to make a favorite dish from home, and he decided on pupusas -  the national dish of El Salvador. He had actually never made them himself, but his wife Mercedes graciously stepped up to help. A pupusa is basically a flatbread made with corn flour. Ours is stuffed with refried beans & mozzarella/vegan mozzerella and served with curtido (a traditional Salvadoran cabbage slaw) and salsa roja. Use a fork and knife or use your hands to tear off pieces; fork some of that curtido on top and drizzle the salsa on‚Ä¶this dish is hearty, delicious and fun to eat and to share. Thank you Luis and Mercedes for sharing this dish with us all. Available through 4/13. #vegetarian or #vegan

inputs.text: BUSINESS HIGHLIGHTS  Enron Freight Markets Despite an eroding economy and increasing scrutiny of Enron, Enron Freight Markets finished a record month in October, completing more than 4,000 transactions (50% growth from September) and adding over 200 new counterparties.  Volumes were especially strong in the last 10 days of the month.  One of the big sources of transaction growth was increased volume from other major freight intermediaries, substantially bolstering EFM's efforts to develop a wholesale market.  Enron Global Markets Coal  Increased liquidity in the prompt months has brought more players into the spot rail market. Traditionally a thin market in the OTC market, the coal group is capitalizing on increased interest by introducing several new EOL rail products. On the CSX rail line, there will be two 12,500 btu products with different sulfur contents - 1.2 pound (or compliance) and 1.6 pound. The CSX contract will be FOB rail in the Big Sandy or Kanawha rail districts. On the Norfolk Southern rail line, there will be two similar 12,500 btu products, however, FOB rail in the Thacker or Kenova rail districts. The coal group intends to bring these products on line within a week for the cash book, and hopefully extend them to the forward markets.  Enron Industrial Markets Lumber Enron's Lumber Trading Group recorded a record 33 transactions on Clickpaper.com for the week ended November 11, 2001 for a gross notional value of approximately $1,200,000. This compares to the group's prior weekly average of 5 online transactions with a notional value of approximately $140,000.  The increase in activity is due to the launch of the Lumber Group's New Futures-Like Fixed Price Forward Contracts, which began trading last week.  "We are very excited about the overwhelming market acceptance of our new Forward Contracts which we expect will revolutionize the way lumber is traded" says John Jacobsen, a manager with EIM's Lumber Trading Group.  We expect to see continued increases in our online trading activity as we start actively marketing them. What makes this week's activity even more promising is the fact that the cash market has been fairly quiet due to the uncertainty surrounding a softwood lumber dispute between the US and Canada."    WELCOME New Hires EGM  - Troy Rawlings, Tom Beam, Jo Crowder EIM   - Leonardo Cardosa, Roger Pederson, Michael Arlia  Transfers (to or within) ENA - Jacob Shupe, David Hernandez, John Suarez, Erika Edwards EIM - Thomas Briggs, Jessica Nunez, Ben Thomason EGM - Diana Luu, Sheila Pardo   NUGGETS & NOTES  EnronOnline Figures Below are the latest figures for EnronOnline as of November 5  *   Total Life to Date Transactions > 1,650,000 *   Life to Date Notional Value of Transactions > $ 913 billion  Enron Wholesale Services Best Practice Tips  Ordering/Locating SkyTel/Blackberry Items in the iBuyit eProcurement Catalog Pagers and Accompanying Service Plans: EWS eProcurement users should go to the catalog under Office Supplies. Enter "Skytel pagers" as the Quick Search text. Tip:  All users must select a service plan in addition to the pager.  Handheld Devices:   EWS eProcurement users should go to the catalog under IT Hardware. Enter "Blackberry" as the Quick Search text.  Tip: No need to select a separate service plan. A service plan is combined in the catalog with each handheld device.  Information Required When Ordering SkyTel Items Pagers and Handheld Devices:  The user's EID* and name are required for all SkyTel items. After adding the item(s) to the Shopping Cart, the requester must click the Line Item Details icon (magnifying glass) and enter the user's EID and name under the Purchase Order Text tab. The order cannot be processed without this information. This will ensure that the ongoing monthly service plan charges are assigned correctly to the user's cost center. *If EID is unknown, users should go to eHRonline to view their EIDs.  Tip: If you wish to swap out a pager for a handheld device, make sure to include your existing pager phone number in the PO Text.   NEWS FROM THE GLOBAL FLASH  Update on Enron Europe  Following on from last week's memo on the health of the business, here's a snapshot of the activities we are pursuing currently to provide customers and investors with confidence in our business:  We are continuing to work on trading liquidity, which to date is going well.  We are transacting with most of our counterparties, but we are spending a significant amount of commercial and commercial support time working on putting credit agreements in place.  These credit agreements tend to focus on netting out exposures between different Enron business units (for example UK gas and UK power) and providing collateral arrangements whereby neither one of us can owe more than a pre-agreed amount without starting to "pay as you go".  During these tough times, our priorities right now are to:         - Preserve cash (as our credit rating has been downgraded, our ability to keep maximum cash liquidity is critical).        - Insure that we are getting paid when we should get paid.  In other words, we are focusing efforts on accounts receivable that should have been paid and are now  overdue (something that is always important, but even more so now).  - Reduce our expenses to the greatest extent possible.  - Keep making money.  So please let us know how we can help you help us get the job done.  Remember, the key thing for Enron at present is that we put all our efforts into making money, keeping costs down and ensuring that all cash due to us is collected on time.  Focusing on the business at hand will be critical to helping us demonstrate our overall strength.  Enron Nordic Energy Restructuring Enron Nordic Energy last week took steps to restructure its operations with respect to Finland.  Moving forward, Enron Nordic Energy will continue to service the Finnish market from its Oslo office, offering a range of products including portfolio and risk management services.  This move is not indicative of a withdrawal of Enron's business from the Finnish market, but rather has been initiated in an effort to rationalise Enron's functions and services in the region.    Enron Succeeds in Completing its First Bi-Lateral Power Transaction Inside Italy  Congratulations are due to the Italian desk for concluding its first power transaction inside Italy.  The team succeeding in buying 5MW of peak energy for December 2001 from Italian wholesaler, Energ.it, and are selling it to Enel Trade, the trading arm of the incumbent energy company, ENEL.  Energ.it is mainly active in Sardinia and off-takes power from the AES plant in Ottana, Sardinia.  "Although this is only a small deal it demonstrates the market's appetite to transact." says Daniela Uguccioni, Enron's Italian power trader.  "Due to the slow progress of liberalisation in Italy, we are still limited to doing back-to-back transactions such as this, however this is definitely a step in the right direction" adds Paul Mead, Director of Regional Power Trading.  "The exciting part of this deal is that ENEL will now trade with us inside Italy, something we have been trying to do with them for years."  New Online Metals Product Last week saw the launch by Enron Metals of online 'averaging' contracts for Copper and Aluminium.  'Fixed for Float' and 'Month on Month' averaging contracts are now available for the 'nearby months' (i.e.up to three months ahead) providing a useful tool for hedgers.  The introduction of this product online, which is of particular interest for producers and consumers, came in response to customer demand.  The initial response has been positive as last week saw the first trades and we are already seeing requests for the product to be made available for other metals.  Polish Power Market Gathers Momentum as Enron Signs Second Master Trading Agreement Enron Poland, which recently closed its first-ever OTC transaction with Poland's largest generator PKE, has signed a second Master Trading Agreement with one of the top ten regional distribution companies, Energa Gdansk.  The agreement will provide the basis for future bi-lateral electricity transactions.  "We hope to close our first deal with Gdansk in Q4", says Jarek Dybowski, Enron's director of power trading in Poland.   BUSINESS HIGHLIGHTS FROM DOWN UNDER Power Desk Sees Promising Market Growth In the energy market, Enron Australia continues to build its presence year-on-year.  Enron Australia's results at the end of the third quarter showed a 50% increase in volumes, an 80% increase in transactions, and a 300% increase in P&L.  The advent of a competitive ancillary services market in Q4 provides scope for increasing the power team's activity further by the end of the year.  Pacific Solar REC Trade Enron Australia has secured a renewable energy deal with Pacific Solar, a company that is developing solar photovoltaic systems for the rooftops of the world. The transaction gives Enron the right to purchase all of the renewable energy certificates (RECs) generated by the PV units sold in Australia. Pacific Solar is also selling its systems in Europe though Italian company, Eurosolare. The deal is the first exclusive offtake agreement Enron has secured in the nascent Australian REC market.   LEGAL STUFF The information contained in this newsletter is confidential and proprietary to Enron Corp. and its subsidiaries.  It is intended for internal use only and should not be disclosed.   <Embedded Paintbrush Picture>

inputs.text: Photos by Pete McBride @pedromcbride | I've spent more than a decade documenting my ‚Äúbackyard‚Äù river‚Äîthe Colorado‚Äîtrying to make more people aware of how much we collectively ask of this lifeline of the American Southwest. It is one of the most loved and litigated bodies of water in the world, and yet it continues to struggle.  Photos: (1) Author Jon Waterman walks the dry Colorado River Delta; (2) a defunct boat ramp at Glen Canyon Dam in Arizona; (3) the Central Arizona Project carries water 336 miles (541 km) to Phoenix and Tucson; (4) dried tendrils in the Colorado River Delta in Mexico, where the river no longer reaches the sea.   American Rivers named the Colorado River the number one most endangered river in the United States, highlighting the threat climate change and outdated water management pose to 30 federally recognized tribal nations, seven states, and Mexico, and to the drinking water for 40 million people. Also threatened is vital habitat for wildlife, as the Colorado River Basin is home to 30 native fish species‚Äîtwo-thirds of which are threatened or endangered‚Äîand more than 400 bird species. To learn more, follow @pedromcbride and go to @americanrivers. #mostendangeredriver #water #drought #conservation #awareness #SeeingSilence #ColoradoRiver #petemcbride

inputs.text: For #TodaysSpecial we‚Äôre talking Tapas, a cuisine (or way of life) @bar_isabel knows a thing or two about. Let your mind wander back to times spent sitting in a plaza en espa√±a, and we‚Äôll provide the perfect topic to bring up over your next plate of Pan tumaca.  Spanish Tapas Mythsüëáüèº13th Century king Alfonso X of Castille could only manage to eat and drink in small amounts whilst unwell. This continued after his recovery and resulted in one of the first forms of Tapas.  In the 19th Century, Tapas, specifically ham, was placed on top of glasses to keep dust or flies out.  Tapas bars previously had little or no seating. When customers ordered a snack they would have no option but to put their plate on top of their glass ‚Äì hence the tradition. inputs.text: While these Crispy Zucchini Fries are amazing as a tasty snack or appetizer at group gatherings, we also find ourselves eating these for dinner sometimes. üôå Grab the full recipe below or on our blog. üíô ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä Ingredients *2 zucchini *1/2 cup flour *1/4 tsp salt *1/2 cup Califia Farms Extra Creamy Oatmilk *1 cup breadcrumbs *1/2 tsp garlic *1/4 tsp smoked paprika *1 tsp Italian seasoning *1/4 cup vegan mayo *1/4 tsp each dried parsley, dill, and garlic *1/8 tsp smoked paprika *1/2 tsp apple cider vinegar *1-2 tbsps Califia Farms Extra Creamy Oatmilk ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä Method *Cut zucchini into sticks about 1-inch thick. Sprinkle generously with salt and let rest for 20 minutes. *Combine the first three ingredients to make the batter. *Prepare the breadcrumb mixture with breadcrumbs, garlic, paprika, and Italian seasoning, whisking to combine. *Rinse zucchini and dry well, then dredge through batter and then through breadcrumbs, adding to a baking sheet once fully coated. *Roast zucchini for 20-25 minutes at 425 degrees Fahrenheit. *Make vegan ranch sauce by combining the remaining ingredients (vegan mayo + following ingredients). Add salt as desired and serve alongside finished zucchini. Enjoy!

inputs.text: {international day of awareness of food loss and waste 2021}  We celebrate today what we celebrate every day. Sustainability, zero food waste and respect for our Mother Earth.   Our philosophy at Terra is based on maximising all ingredients and reusing all leftovers until only fibres or non-edible parts are donate to our compost.   Back in May 2020, we become a zero food waste restaurant.  This dish - the garfish tail - become the icon for our concept.   We got a garfish from sustainable fishing in the Nordic sea, and we use every single part of it. As the nose to tail concept. We decided to be a bit provocative and to raise awareness to our guests. Therefore we served the tail, as our Italian roots and grandpa thought us, is the most delicious part of it. A roasted tail, glazed with homemade tamari and served with a broth of garfish (made from the fish bones and heads). The filet is served as an other dish in the tasting menu. Once again provoking to show that you can serve the same ingredient in the same menu. Without being boring. On the contrary, serving with different flavours and textures.  That is our zero food waste approach. And what sustainability is for us. Reusing and transforming in a creative way every single ingredient until only non edible parts are donates to our compost for our kitchen garden.  Let‚Äôs be the change we wanna become.   Since September 2021, we have been awarded as green Michelin star restaurant by the @michelinguide üçÄ  T√®rra | zero food waste minimal, sustainable & innovative  A green star in the Michelin guide.  @_terrarestaurant_  Chef @valerio_serino   A project by @valerio_serino & @__lucy_in_the_sky__   #_terrarestaurant_ #_terraproject_ #sustainable #michelinguide  #greenrestaurant #zerowaste #adgitaly #valerioserino #zerofoodwaste #michelingreenstar #flwday #flwday2021

inputs.text: Everything is better in mini form and these individual Banana Puddings are no exception. üíõ Our silky Vanilla Oatmilk is the perfect base to the deliciously-smooth pudding in this recipe! üçå ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä Ingredients *3 tablespoons cornstarch  *¬º cup granulated sugar  *‚Öõ teaspoon kosher salt  *2 cups Califia Farms Vanilla Oatmilk *1 ¬Ω tablespoons vegan butter  *1 heaping cup crushed vegan vanilla wafers  *2 medium bananas, sliced  *Vegan whipped cream, for garnish  ‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä Method  *Add the first three ingredients to a large saucepan and whisk until combined. Slowly pour in the Vanilla Oatmilk while whisking constantly, until fully incorporated. *Place the saucepan over medium heat and, while whisking constantly, let the mixture come to a boil. Once it's boiling, continue whisking for two minutes, then remove from heat.  *Immediately transfer the pudding to a heatproof bowl and whisk in the vegan butter. *Let the pudding cool to room temperature, then cover and place in the fridge. Allow the pudding to fully chill before serving, this should take about 3 hours. *When ready to serve, vigorously whisk the pudding until smooth. To assemble, fill each cup with about ¬º cup of crushed wafers, a layer of sliced banana, and a portion of pudding. Top each cup with vegan whipped cream and a light garnish of crushed wafers. Enjoy!

Rub pork with salt and pepper and place in a pressure cooker. 4. Pour the marinade over pork. Add 2 cups of water‚ÄîCook for 45 minutes from the start of the whistling sound. 5. Prepare the pickled onions and the sauce while the meat is cooking. Cut thin pieces of red onion and put them in a mixture of water, vinegar, and oregano. 6. For the sauce, season cajun peppers with mustard, salt, and pepper on a frying pan with a small amount of olive oil. Grind the seasoned peppers and add orange juice to the mix. 7. Once the meat is ready, shred it and return to the pressure cooker with the cooking juices. 8. In a hot pan, place shredded cheese until it browns and a rigid shell forms. 9. Remove the shredded meat from the cooker and put it in a tray. 10. Form the cheese in the shape of a taco and place the shredded pork in it.  #yum #eat #foodpic #dinner #foodpics #lunch #dinner #foodphotography #foodlover #tasty #hungry #foodblogger #healthyfood #foods #cooking #eeeeeats #TasteOfHome #StellaArtois

inputs.text: The Caribbean Noir is everything you love about the espresso martini, but with a little more coconut and a lot more bourbon. This cocktail is one of the delicious drinks that helped Miguel Soto become 2020's Best Black Bartender in the nation. Mix one up with the recipe below and be sure to join @blackrestaurantweek‚Äôs Cocktail Lounge on Mondays to watch the 2021 Power of the Palate cocktail competition live.   ùêÇùêöùê´ùê´ùê¢ùêõùêõùêûùêöùêß ùêçùê®ùê¢ùê´ ‚òïÔ∏è 1-1/2 parts Maker's Mark¬Æ Bourbon 1 part South African Rooibos organic red tea-infused Pedro Xim√©nez Jerez Sherry 2 dashes coffee- and coconut-infused aromatic bitters  Lemon peel and banana leaf for garnish  Pedro Xim√©nez Jerez Sherry Infusion: To infuse the Pedro Xim√©nez, use 8 oz of PX and 2-1/2 tbsp of red tea. Heat the PX with the loose leaf tea for 5 minutes on medium-low heat. Allow it to cool down. Place the infusion in the refrigerator for 1 hour. Double strain the mixture. Add 5 ml of active charcoal to the mixture, shake it and bottle it.  Coffee and coconut-infused aromatic bitters: Place 6 oz of medium-body coffee beans inside a 10 oz mason jar. Pour 8 oz of aromatic bitters and 2 oz of organic coconut extract. Seal it and shake it really hard. Let it sit for 24 hours and shake the mixture a few times during that period.  Garnish: To preserve the integrity of the banana leaf garnish, apply raw honey in the area that was attached to the plant and then put it in iced water, submerging only the same part where the honey was applied. Use raw honey to attach the leaf to the glass.  #EspressoMartini #EspressoMartinis #EspressoLove #MixologistWorld #CocktailRecipe #CocktailTime #CocktailsofInstagram
